<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-23T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-23T05:00:00-05:00" n="928" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d928">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">390D.11/205: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-23T12:00:00+02:00">November 23, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:33
                                    p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>210. Embassy’s telegram number 163, October 7, 6 p.m., and despatch
                                No. 1590, November 8.<note n="67" xml:id="d928fn67">Latter not
                                    printed.</note> I took up this matter yesterday with the Foreign
                                Minister and expressed the hope that notwithstanding the urgent
                                international problems now preoccupying him he would be able to look
                                into this question soon. He said that he hoped that he would be able
                                to do so in the near future.<note n="68" xml:id="d928fn68">No
                                    further action, however, was taken by the Turkish authorities on
                                    this proposed agreement.</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>